Title: DateTime.layerCurrentZone
Category: function
Module Path: effect/DateTime
Export Kind: const
Category Tag: current time zone

Description: Create a Layer from the given time zone. This layer provides the `CurrentTimeZone` service with the specified time zone.

Signature: layerCurrentZone: (resource: NoInfer<TimeZone>) => Layer.Layer<CurrentTimeZone> = Layer.succeed( CurrentTimeZone )

Example:
```ts
import { DateTime, Effect } from "effect"

const zone = DateTime.zoneMakeNamedUnsafe("Europe/London")
const layer = DateTime.layerCurrentZone(zone)

const program = Effect.gen(function*() {
  const now = yield* DateTime.nowInCurrentZone
  return DateTime.formatIsoZoned(now)
})

// Use the layer to provide the time zone
Effect.provide(program, layer)
```

