Title: Ref.makeUnsafe
Category: function
Module Path: effect/Ref
Export Kind: const
Category Tag: constructors

Description: Creates a new Ref with the specified initial value (unsafe version). This function creates a Ref synchronously without wrapping in Effect. Use this only when you're sure about the safety of immediate creation.

Signature: makeUnsafe = <A>(value: A): Ref<A> => { const self = Object.create(RefProto) self.ref = MutableRef.make(value) return self }

Example:
```ts
import { Ref } from "effect"

// Create a ref directly without Effect
const counter = Ref.makeUnsafe(0)

// Get the current value
const value = Ref.getUnsafe(counter)
console.log(value) // 0

// Note: This is unsafe and should be used carefully
// Prefer Ref.make for Effect-wrapped creation
```

